{"first_name":"Bob","last_name":"Crowley","permalink":"bob-crowley","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/bob-crowley","homepage_url":"http://www.mustanggroup.com","birthplace":"Chappaqua, NY","twitter_username":"","blog_url":"http://www.dieseldoeswestern.com","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Scribe Software","born_year":1957,"born_month":4,"born_day":23,"tag_list":"bob-crowley, bowstreet, arbortext, kenan-systems, cabledata, safeguard-scientific, the-mustang-group, ultra-running, boston, cable-tv, web-services, etc","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Tue Oct 27 13:41:48 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Tue Jul 26 19:58:02 UTC 2011","overview":"<p>Bob is co-founder and managing partner of The Mustang Group, a Boston-based private equity firm focused on small middle market transactions. </p>\n\n<p>Crowleyâ€™s career began as an operator spanning a decade each in media (cable television), telecommunications and software, serving primarily the financial services sector (brokers, banks, multi-nationals and insurance).  </p>\n\n<p>Prior to founding Mustang, Bob was the managing director of Safeguard Scientific&#8217;s [NYSE:SFE] software portfolio where he lead the technology operating company&#8217;s strategy, acquisition and partner company management for software properties. Crowley was the former president and CEO of Bowstreet, the Web services pioneer in software automation, from 1999 to 2001. </p>\n\n<p>Prior to Bowstreet, Bob was the President and CEO of ArborText, the leading enterprise e-Content management system for the Web. Prior to joining Arbortext, </p>\n\n<p>Bob led business development, sales and international operations at Kenan Systems, a leading convergent customer care, billing, and analysis software supplier to wireline, wireless, cable television, and e-Commerce providers. During Bob&#8217;s two year tenure, the company grew from $15 million in revenues to $120 million. In January 1999, Kenan was sold to Lucent for $1.4 billion. </p>\n\n<p>Bob also led business development at CableData, the largest software and billing fulfillment provider to the cable television market. During his tenure, the company grew four-fold, serving over 35 million global subscribers. </p>\n\n<p>He began his media and communications career as a general manager for a top 20 multiple system operator (MSO), American Cablesystems. Bob began his career at Martin-Marietta Aerospace in Bethesda, MD. </p>\n\n<p>He earned a Bachelor&#8217;s Degree in Business Administration and Finance and Marketing from Villanova University. Bob is married to Marcy and they have two sons, Patrick and Drew.  Bob participates competes in a variety of ultra distance running events (50- and 100-mile trail runs).</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[95,150],"assets/images/resized/0006/3915/63915v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[150,236],"assets/images/resized/0006/3915/63915v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[150,236],"assets/images/resized/0006/3915/63915v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":"<p>Bob Crowley</p>"},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"BS in BA","subject":"Finance","institution":"Villanova University","graduated_year":1979,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null}],"relationships":[{"is_past":false,"title":"Board Member","firm":{"name":"Country Club Enterprise","permalink":"country-club-enterprise","type_of_entity":"company","image":null}},{"is_past":false,"title":"Board Member","firm":{"name":"MetraTech","permalink":"metratech","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,42],"assets/images/resized/0013/5527/135527v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[227,65],"assets/images/resized/0013/5527/135527v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[227,65],"assets/images/resized/0013/5527/135527v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":false,"title":"Board Member","firm":{"name":"Vermont Teddy Bear","permalink":"vermont-teddy-bear","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[84,84],"assets/images/resized/0006/5898/65898v1-max-150x150.png"],[[84,84],"assets/images/resized/0006/5